The World Trade Center Memorial Foundation has gained support from former US presidents, including Bush and Clinton.
The memorial will honor the victims of the 9/11 attacks, with a focus on the twin towers' symbolism.
The board includes various prominent figures tasked with raising funds for the project.
Governor Pataki emphasized the importance of creating a lasting memorial to preserve the impact of the attacks.
The memorial design includes elements from the original towers, ensuring a poignant tribute to the lives lost.
The project aims to educate future generations about the tragedy and its significance.
